        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nNot sure if seen (or posted...):\nI agree with you that we may not care about this port.\nBUT, as some are deterministic, we cannot have one (or several) that is not as k8s may decide to use as value for this not deterministic port one of the value we have statically written (that's how I've spotted it as it broke my deployment)\n\nfor the value,  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}03 is already used as  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}00  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}01  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}02  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}04  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}05  {{.Value.nodePortPrefix }}06 up to around 30...",
